     {q:"What is 13 ÷ 4, including the remainder?", options:["3 remainder 2","3 remainder 1","4 remainder 1","4 remainder 0"], answer:1},
     {q:"A remainder must always be ___ than the number you are dividing by.", options:["Larger, with no connection to the divisor","A concept unrelated to the size of the divisor","Exactly equal to, with no exceptions","Smaller"], answer:3},
     {q:"If 17 stickers are shared equally among 5 friends, how many stickers are left over?", options:["0","3","2","1"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might understanding remainders be useful when sharing items in real life, like cookies among friends?", options:["It shows how many items are left over after sharing them as evenly as possible","Remainders never occur when sharing items among friends","Remainders only apply to multiplication, never to division","This concept has no connection to real-world sharing situations"], answer:0}
