     {q:"Using public transportation can help reduce the number of ___ on the road.", options:["Buildings, which are not vehicles on the road","A concept unrelated to transportation","Pedestrians, with no connection to reducing traffic","Cars"], answer:3},
     {q:"Which is an example of a type of public transportation?", options:["A private car owned by a single family","A subway","A concept unrelated to moving people around a community","A form of transportation that does not actually exist"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why might a large city rely heavily on public transportation?", options:["This concept has no relevance to understanding urban communities","It helps move large numbers of people efficiently without requiring everyone to drive their own car","Large cities never need any form of transportation system","Public transportation has no benefit for cities with many people"], answer:1},
     {q:"Why might using public transportation instead of individual cars be helpful for the environment?", options:["Moving many people together in one vehicle can reduce overall traffic and pollution compared to many separate cars","The number of vehicles on the road has no effect on the environment","This concept has no connection to understanding the environment","Public transportation always creates more pollution than individual cars"], answer:0}
