     {q:"Why might farmland be considered an important resource for a province like Ontario?", options:["It allows the province to produce food for its own communities and potentially for other places too","This concept has no relevance to understanding Ontario’s economy","Farmland has no connection to producing food or supporting an economy","Provinces never need farmland to support their communities"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why might farmers in Ontario need to consider factors like soil quality and weather when growing crops?", options:["Soil quality and weather have no effect on farming success","Crops always grow the exact same way no matter the conditions","This concept has no relevance to understanding agriculture","These factors can significantly affect how well crops grow and how much food is produced"], answer:3}
