     {q:"Why must the same rule be applied to every input in an input-output table?", options:["Changing the rule for each input never affects the table’s pattern","An input-output table never actually follows any specific rule","Using the same rule keeps the pattern between the inputs and outputs consistent","This concept has no connection to understanding number patterns"], answer:2},
     {q:"If an input-output table shows inputs of 2, 4, and 6 producing outputs of 4, 8, and 12, what rule is being used?", options:["Multiply by 2","Add 2","Subtract 2","Divide by 2"], answer:0}
