     {q:"Why might shipping goods across the Great Lakes be an efficient way to move large amounts of cargo?", options:["This concept has no relevance to understanding trade routes","The Great Lakes have no connection to transporting goods","A single ship can carry very large loads across long distances at once","Shipping by water is always slower and less efficient than any other method"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might cities along the Great Lakes, like Toronto and Hamilton, benefit from being located near this shipping route?", options:["This concept has no relevance to understanding Ontario’s geography","Easy access to shipping can support trade and industry, helping the local economy grow","Being located near the Great Lakes provides no benefit to a city’s economy","Shipping routes have no connection to how cities develop"], answer:1}
