     {q:"A digital clock displays the time using only ___.", options:["Numbers","Moving hands, which is how an analog clock works instead","A concept unrelated to how a digital clock works","Pictures, with no connection to displaying numbers"], answer:0},
     {q:"If an analog clock shows the short hand near the 3 and the long hand on the 12, what time is it?", options:["3:12","12:03","12:15","3:00"], answer:3},
     {q:"Why might it take more practice to read an analog clock than a digital clock?", options:["Digital clocks are never easier for anyone to read","An analog clock always shows the exact same information as a digital clock with no extra steps","This concept has no relevance to understanding how clocks work","An analog clock requires understanding what both the hour hand and minute hand represent together"], answer:3},
     {q:"Why do both analog and digital clocks show the same time, even though they look very different?", options:["Both types of clocks are simply different ways of representing the same passage of time","This concept has no relevance to understanding how time is measured","The way a clock displays time has no connection to the actual time","Analog and digital clocks always show two completely different times"], answer:0}
