     {q:"Treaties often involve land, rights, and ___ that both groups agreed to follow.", options:["Only decorations, with no connection to an agreement","Responsibilities","A concept unrelated to what a treaty includes","Weather forecasts, with no connection to treaties"], answer:1},
     {q:"Which best describes the purpose of a treaty?", options:["To formally record an agreement between two or more groups","A story with no real historical importance","A concept unrelated to reaching an agreement","An event with no connection to government or Indigenous peoples"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why is it important for students to learn about treaties between Canada and Indigenous peoples?", options:["This concept has no relevance to social studies learning","Learning about treaties provides no useful understanding of Canada","Treaties are an important part of Canada’s history and continue to affect relationships and rights today","Treaties have no connection to understanding Canada’s history"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why might it be important for all parties involved in a treaty to understand and respect its terms?", options:["This concept has no relevance to understanding historical agreements","The terms of a treaty have no real effect on the people involved","Treaties never need to be understood or followed by anyone","A treaty is only meaningful if the groups involved follow the agreement they made together"], answer:3}
