     {q:"Name one service a municipal budget might fund, such as parks or libraries.", options:["Parks","Video games","A concept unrelated to municipal budgets","Private vacations"], answer:0},
     {q:"Does a municipal government use tax money to plan its budget?", options:["Yes","No, budgets never use tax money","Only businesses use budgets","A concept unrelated to government"], answer:0},
     {q:"Why must a municipal government carefully plan how it spends its budget?", options:["This concept has no relevance to local government","Budgets have no connection to community needs","So tax money is used fairly and effectively for shared community needs","Municipal governments never need to plan spending"], answer:2},
     {q:"What might happen if a municipal government spent its whole budget on only one single service?", options:["Municipal budgets have no effect on services","Every other service would automatically get more funding instead","Other important services, like roads or libraries, might not get enough funding","This concept has no connection to how communities are run"], answer:2}
